Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces) into small pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}.

Pick the @mint{1}(picked from stalks and roughly chopped) leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Roughly chop the @olives{30}. Crumble the @feta cheese{100%g}.

Heat a splash of @oil{a splash} in a medium #saucepan{} on a medium-high heat. When hot, add the onion, cook stirring occasionally until soft, ~{4-5%mins}.

Add half of the garlic and cook stirring frequently for ~{1%min}. Stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%g}, @chicken stock powder{1} and @water for the bulgur{240%ml}.

Bring to the boil. Pop a #lid{} on the pan and set aside for ~{12-15%mins} or until ready to serve.

Heat a splash of @oil{a splash} in a large #frying pan{} over a medium-high heat.

When hot add the @diced chicken thigh{210%g} and cook stirring occasionally until browned all over, ~{6-7%mins}.

When browned add the @honey{15%ml}, @smoked paprika{1}(or to taste), the remaining garlic, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} and a splash of water.

Cook stirring frequently until the chicken is glazed, ~{2-3%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Fluff up the bulgur wheat with a #fork{} and gently stir through the baby plum tomatoes, olives, mint and half of the feta.

Season to taste with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Share the bulgur between your #bowls{} and top with the glazed chicken.

Crumble over the remaining feta and enjoy!